{
  "texts": [
    "While acknowledging practical challenges in implementing AI in educational evaluation, the study suggests that transparency and comprehensive explanations can enhance fairness perceptions.",
    "This study contributes to the understanding of fairness perception in AI algorithmic evaluation in the digital context.",
    "The findings demonstrate that the evaluator, whether it is an AI algorithm or a teacher, significantly influences college students' perceptions of fairness in diagnostic, formative, and summative evaluations.",
    "Specifically, students perceive AI algorithms as fairer evaluators compared to teachers, with formative evaluation showing the strongest Chai et al. 10.3389/fpsyg.2024.1221177 Frontiers in Psychology 14 frontiersin.org effect.",
    "This perception is mediated by the perceived information transparency of AI algorithms, which is perceived to be higher than that of teachers."
  ]
}